  "questionProse": [
    "コンソールに出力される値は何ですか？"
  ],
  "hintsProse": [],
  "explanationProse": [
    "The string without a `T` time value may appear to be Jan 1st, 2020 - but date-only strings are interpreted as UTC, and when adjusted to our local timezone (GMT-7) we find we're still in 2019.\n\n      Date-time strings without an explicit timezone are interpreted in local time.\n  \n      The `T00:00` form causes the second value to be interpreted as local midnight.\n\n      The first date is interpreted as `Tue Dec 31 2019 17:00:00 GMT-0700 (Mountain Standard Time)`.\n      The second date is interpreted as `Wed Jan 01 2020 00:00:00 GMT-0700 (Mountain Standard Time)`."
  ]
